<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n06055g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06055g">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06055g"> 55(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> jouet change sexe / personne</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Les joujoux qui amusent le plus l&apos;enfant sont ceux o&ugrave; il a le plus &agrave; inventer. &hellip; Une vieille charrette est tour &agrave; tour locomotive, automobile et chariot. <mark>La poup&eacute;e change de sexe, d&apos;&acirc;ge, de caract&egrave;re et de costume</mark>, au gr&eacute; de la petite maman. <font color="green">[The toys that entertain the child the most are those where he has the most to invent. ... An old cart is alternately locomotive, automobile and cart. The doll changes sex, age, character and costume, at the whim of the little mother.]</font> <small> Fr&eacute;d&eacute;ric Queyrat, <a name="FQLJ" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#FQLJ"><cite title="source">Les Jeux des Enfants</cite></a> (1920) 143</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c01126c" href="c01all.htm#c01126c">VI.C.01:126(c)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
